International golf is set to return to Durban, after a near ten-year absence. The city will host a new golf tournament on the Sunshine and Challenge Tours, At the famous Durban Country Club and Mount Edgecombe Country Club. The Jonsson Workwear Open will provide promising young golfers an opportunity on the international stage while reaching out to wider communities for growth and development. eNCA's Siphokazi Malinga reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - International golf is set to return to Durban after a nearly 10-year absence. The city will host a new golf tournament on the Sunshine and Challenge Tours, The Jonsson Work-wear Open will provide promising young golfers an opportunity on the international stage. The timing could not have been better for the Durban Country Club. The famous course is celebrating its centenary year and is now back on the international scene. * eNCA's Siphokazi Malinga reports.